HEADWORD: Chaplainship
<hw>Chap"lain*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office or
business of a chaplain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Bethesda of some knight's <qex>chaplainship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The possession or revenue of a chapel.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chapless</ent>⟦br⟧
